
Function	   Example	                                   Description

Length	        "hello".Length	                 Gets the number of characters in the string
ToUpper()	"hello".ToUpper()	               Converts to uppercase
ToLower()	"HELLO".ToLower()	                Converts to lowercase
Substring()	"hello".Substring(1, 3)  	Extracts a substring starting at index 1 of length 3
IndexOf()	"hello".IndexOf("l")	        Finds the index of a substring
Replace()	"hello".Replace("l", "x")	Replaces all instances of a substring
Contains()	"hello".Contains("he")	        Checks if the string contains a substring
Trim()	        " hello ".Trim()	                Removes whitespace from both ends
Split()	        "a,b,c".Split(',')	                Splits the string into an array
Join() string.Join("-", new[] { "a", "b" })	Joins array elements into a string
Equals()	"test".Equals("TEST", StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase)	Compares two strings with options